{"start": "20251203_163439", "end": "20251203_163439", "time": 3.743171691894531e-05, "tool_name": "return_answer", "result": {"success": true, "preview": "\"It is not possible to restrict the analysis to LGG (Brain Lower Grade Glioma) patients using the provided clinical_database, because that database only contains lung cancer cohorts (diagnosis values are Lung Adenocarcinoma, Lung Squamous Cell Carcinoma, or None) and has no field for the LGG/BRCA-type cancer acronyms. Therefore, I cannot identify which IGF2 expression records in the molecular_database correspond to LGG patients and cannot compute the requested averages by histology type specifically for LGG.\\n\\nIf you can provide a clinical table that includes LGG patients (for example, a table with a cancer_type_acronym or diagnosis field containing LGG/Brain Lower Grade Glioma) linked by Patient_description to ParticipantBarcode, I can then:\\n1) join that table to the RNASeq_Expression IGF2 data,\\n2) filter to LGG only,\\n3) exclude rows with missing/invalid IGF2 values and histology values in square brackets,\\n4) calculate log10(normalized_count + 1) for each sample, and\\n5) report the mean per histology type with \\u22654 decimal places.\""}, "args": {"answer": "It is not possible to restrict the analysis to LGG (Brain Lower Grade Glioma) patients using the provided clinical_database, because that database only contains lung cancer cohorts (diagnosis values are Lung Adenocarcinoma, Lung Squamous Cell Carcinoma, or None) and has no field for the LGG/BRCA-type cancer acronyms. Therefore, I cannot identify which IGF2 expression records in the molecular_database correspond to LGG patients and cannot compute the requested averages by histology type specifically for LGG.\n\nIf you can provide a clinical table that includes LGG patients (for example, a table with a cancer_type_acronym or diagnosis field containing LGG/Brain Lower Grade Glioma) linked by Patient_description to ParticipantBarcode, I can then:\n